A vintage 1990s-era desktop computer tower with its side panel removed, revealing tangled cables and a newly installed hard drive awkwardly wedged among older components. The scene is lit by warm amber desk lamp light, casting dramatic shadows. On the desk beside the open computer sits a scattered collection of floppy disks, a coffee mug with cold remnants, and a worn technical manual. The aesthetic evokes late-night troubleshooting frustration—dust particles visible in the lamplight, a CRT monitor glowing softly in the background showing an error dialog box (no readable text, just colored rectangles). Color palette of beige computer hardware, warm yellows, and deep shadows. Photographic style reminiscent of 35mm film grain from the early 2000s.
